"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506589","Department of Health","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Department does not hold this information.</p><p> </p><p>National Health Service hospital treatment is free to those people who are ordinarily resident in the United Kingdom, or those exempt from charge under the NHS (Charges to Overseas Visitors) Regulations 2015, as amended. Anyone else should present a European Health Insurance Card, S1 or S2 form or pay direct for their NHS care. Those who need care and treatment urgently will still receive it even if they are chargeable and cannot pay straight away.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","32956 ; 32957 ; 32958 ; 33193 ; 33194","2016-04-18T10:46:39.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506589/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506589/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506589/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-08","NHS: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people working in the NHS were refused NHS treatment on the basis of their immigration status in (a) 2013, (b) 2014, (c) 2015 and (d) 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","32955"
