"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/487024","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-04-11","<p>The £26.2 million aid package we secured from the European Commission has helped to provide some immediate relief. A number of supermarkets have also pledged to pay a premium over and above the current market price.</p><p> </p><p>Longer term, we are working to develop futures markets in the dairy sector to help farmers manage risk.</p><p> </p><p>At the most recent council meeting in the EU, the UK supported a package of new measures to try to help the dairy sector recover.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-04-11T11:07:51.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/487024/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/487024/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/487024/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-24","Dairy Products: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent steps she is taking to ensure that farmers receive fair pricing for their dairy produce.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","32564"
